body: @qraleq The new error message indicates a problem with the model. There is a depthwise convolution in the model where the input channel count is 34 but the filter count is only 32. The node is named Conv__1363. Can you check the original model?

@tracysh I think that I located the problem, but I'm not sure how to fix it. As I mentioned we're using `ssd_mobilenet_v2_fpn` backbone. We have set `use_explicit_padding: true` in the pipeline.config and it's a prerequisite for our model to work as we want.

If I set `use_explicit_padding` to `false`, the model runs with onnx runtime, but the results aren't good. Can you help me resolve this issue?
@qraleq Hmm, it's getting past my areas of expertise, maybe others can step in. If this is a model conversion issue, then maybe also try https://github.com/onnx/tensorflow-onnx.

@tracysh Although there are no errors thrown while creating the model, you're right that this might be a conversion issue, but I'm not sure.

If anyone here knows how to resolve this, help is more than welcome!

@qraleq, can you share a link to the original model file (frozen-model or saved_model format is fine)? 

The  SSD object detection model with MobilenetV2 FPN doesn't show up as one of  the zoo models : https://github.com/tensorflow/models/blob/master/research/object_detection/g3doc/detection_model_zoo.md

@jignparm We've replaced the backbone to MobilenetV2_FPN instead of the MobilenetV1_FPN which is available in the model zoo. I will send you the frozen model a bit later, but you can reproduce this issue by adding `use_explicit_padding: true` to the config file of the model in the `feature_extractor` part and freezing the model again. This should result in the same behavior that we observe using our model.
@jignparm Here is the link to the frozen pb model file: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1SU-pEb93eLQoRMxaK5z80jyjemZ0YuIn/view?usp=sharing.

The TF loader (v 1.14) shows this error when loading the graph_def file. What version of TF are you using to load (or generate) this model? TF2.0 support in the TF2ONNX convertor is not fully active at this time.
